description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/kiss_transport.c
Lines: 545-563

kiss_transport_deinit() disables UART interrupts but does not stop the RX thread:

    void kiss_transport_deinit(void)
    {
        ...
        /* Disable UART interrupts */
        if (ctx->uart_dev != NULL) {
            uart_irq_rx_disable(ctx->uart_dev);
        }

        /* Note: k_thread_abort() would be needed to stop the RX thread,
         * but that can cause issues. In practice, deinit is rarely called. */

        ctx->initialized = false;
        ...
    }

The RX thread (kiss_rx_thread_fn) continues running and accessing ctx after deinit:
- Reads from rx_ring (line 387)
- Accesses stats_mutex (line 388)
- Calls dispatch_frame which accesses config callbacks (line 397)

If the transport is deinitialized and then reinitialized (or memory reused), this is a use-after-free/race.

Fix: Use a flag + semaphore pattern to gracefully stop the thread, or use k_thread_join() after signaling shutdown.
